Events



&lt;div class="col-md-8 mx-auto text-center"&gt;
  &lt;p class="lead"&gt;Explore our upcoming and past events that celebrate India's rich mathematical heritage through conferences, workshops, and lectures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;div class="col-12"&gt;
  &lt;div class="featured-section"&gt;
    &lt;div class="row align-items-center"&gt;
      &lt;div class="col-md-8"&gt;
        &lt;h2&gt;Announcing: Ganita Sammelan&lt;/h2&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;19-22 January 2025&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;This in-person four-day workshop will have a rich variety of events: plenary talks by distinguished scholars (including Prof Manjul Bhargava, Dr MD Srinivas, Prof MS Sriram, Prof K Ramasubramanian, Prof Amartya K Dutta), presentations by other scholars, release of at least two major new books, a session in remembrance of the towering scholar, the late Prof RC Gupta, results of a national quiz competition for schoolchildren on the history of Indian mathematics, interactive sessions with school students (including fun and games), etc.&lt;/p&gt;

        &lt;div class="featured-buttons"&gt;
          &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/Ganita-Poster.pdf" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Download Poster&lt;/a&gt;
          &lt;a href="https://events.iitgn.ac.in/apply/application_ganitasammelana.php?eventid=26112024" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Register for the event&lt;/a&gt;
          &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/Ganita_Sammelan_Abstracts.pdf" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Book of Abstracts&lt;/a&gt;
          &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/Ganita%20Sammelan%20schedule_18.01.2025.pdf" class="btn btn-outline-primary"&gt;Schedule&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="col-md-4"&gt;
        &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/500x300.jpg?text=Ganita+Sammelan" alt="Ganita Sammelan" class="img-fluid rounded"&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



Past Events


&lt;!-- Event 1 --&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="event-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300.jpg?text=Workshop+for+Teachers" alt="Workshop for School Teachers" class="img-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="event-content"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;Workshop for School Teachers: An Introduction to Mathematics in India&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="event-date"&gt;12-14 February 2024&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;A practical exploration of India's rich mathematical heritage! This workshop combined historical insights, hands-on activities, and interactive talks to provide educators with a deep understanding of Indian mathematics.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/homi-poster-v2-A4.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary"&gt;Download Poster&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Event 2 --&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="event-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300.jpg?text=Infinite+Insights" alt="INFINITE INSIGHTS: A journey through India's mathematical marvels" class="img-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="event-content"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;INFINITE INSIGHTS: A journey through India's mathematical marvels&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="event-date"&gt;16-17 November 2023&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;This conversation series was a platform open to all and discussed the convergence of the past and present in exploring India's knowledge systems.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/Infinite_Insights_HoMI.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary"&gt;Download Poster&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Event 3 --&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="event-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300.jpg?text=Young+Scholars+Conference" alt="Young Scholars' Conference on the History of Mathematics" class="img-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="event-content"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;Young Scholars' Conference on the History of Mathematics&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="event-date"&gt;21 January 2023&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;In this second instalment of the Young Scholars' Conference conducted online, researchers discussed a variety of topics related to Indian Mathematics.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-2"&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/2nd_Young_%20Schedule.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary"&gt;Schedule&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/2nd_Young_Scholars_Book_Abstracts.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary"&gt;Book of Abstracts&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/images/2nd_Young_Scholars_Conference.png" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary"&gt;Photos of Workshop&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Event 4 --&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="event-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300.jpg?text=Apodictic+Discourse" alt="Apodictic Discourse: A Paradigm for Rational Scholarly Communication?" class="img-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="event-content"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;Apodictic Discourse: A Paradigm for Rational Scholarly Communication?&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="event-date"&gt;17 September 2021&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;In this online seminar, the speaker provided the paradigm for communication among scholars to emancipate the dimensions of scientific knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/Poster_Homi_lecture_series_2_Satyanad.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary"&gt;Download Poster&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Event 5 --&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="event-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300.jpg?text=ICM+History" alt="How International Were the Early International Congresses of Mathematicians?" class="img-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="event-content"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;How International Were the Early International Congresses of Mathematicians?&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="event-date"&gt;18 June 2021&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;In this online seminar, the speaker discussed the early history of the International Congresses of Mathematicians, and how they gradually opened up to the wider world.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/HOMI_SS_C_Hollings_18.06.2021.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary"&gt;Download Poster&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Event 6 --&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="event-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300.jpg?text=Young+Scholars+2021" alt="Young Scholars' Conference on the History of Mathematics" class="img-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="event-content"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;Young Scholars' Conference on the History of Mathematics&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="event-date"&gt;17 & 18 April 2021&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;In this two-day online conference, young researchers from around the world presented their research on various themes of ancient Mathematics, with special emphasis on India. The originality of the conference was that several senior scholars in the field commented on the young scholars' presentations and offered further advice.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-2"&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/17-18_April%202021_schedule_Page_2.jpg" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary"&gt;Schedule&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/Young_Scholars_Conference_Book_of_Abstracts_April_2021.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary"&gt;Book of Abstracts&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/images/Snip20210418_6.png" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary"&gt;Photos of Workshop&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Event 7 --&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="event-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300.jpg?text=ICEHIM+2017" alt="International Conference on Exploring the History of Indian Mathematics" class="img-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="event-content"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;International Conference on Exploring the History of Indian Mathematics&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="event-date"&gt;4-6 December 2017&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;This international conference at IIT Gandhinagar, jointly held with the Indian Society for the History of Mathematics, hosted some of the finest scholars in the field from India and overseas, and discussed India's advances in ancient to twentieth-century Indian mathematics.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-2"&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/timetable_ICEHIM.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary"&gt;Schedule&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/Title&Abstract.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary"&gt;Book of Abstracts&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/images/Felicity_hrICEH.jpg" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary"&gt;Photos of Workshop&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Event 8 --&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="event-card"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300.jpg?text=Workshop+2013" alt="Workshop on Promoting History of Science in India" class="img-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="event-content"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;Workshop on Promoting History of Science in India&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="event-date"&gt;16–17 March 2013&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;This workshop presented an authentic picture of scientific advances in pre-modern India, especially in the fields of mathematics and astronomy. Leading scholars and over 50 delegates engaged in discussions on how to promote awareness of ancient India's achievements in science.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-2"&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/History_of_science,%20IITGn_March_2013_Book_of_schedule.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary"&gt;Schedule&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/files/History_of_science,%20IITGn_March_2013_Book_of_Abstracts.pdf" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary"&gt;Book of Abstracts&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;a href="https://sites.iitgn.ac.in/homi/assets/images/HOS_photo.jpg" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary"&gt;Photos of Workshop&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

Our Projects



&lt;div class="col-md-8 mx-auto text-center"&gt;
  &lt;p class="lead"&gt;Explore our research initiatives focused on documenting, analyzing, and preserving India's rich mathematical heritage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



Current Projects


&lt;div class="col-md-6 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="card h-100"&gt;
    &lt;div class="card-body"&gt;
      &lt;h3 class="card-title"&gt;Mathematical Manuscripts Documentation&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="card-text"&gt;This project focuses on the documentation and analysis of mathematical manuscripts from various periods of Indian history. Our team is working to catalog, digitize, and analyze these important historical documents.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p class="card-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Status:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span class="badge bg-primary"&gt;In Progress&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="col-md-6 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="card h-100"&gt;
    &lt;div class="card-body"&gt;
      &lt;h3 class="card-title"&gt;Educational Resource Development&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="card-text"&gt;We are developing comprehensive educational resources about the history of Indian mathematics for schools and universities. These materials aim to make India's mathematical heritage accessible to students at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p class="card-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Status:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span class="badge bg-primary"&gt;In Progress&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="col-md-6 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="card h-100"&gt;
    &lt;div class="card-body"&gt;
      &lt;h3 class="card-title"&gt;Digital Archive of Mathematical Artifacts&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="card-text"&gt;This project involves creating a comprehensive digital archive of historical mathematical artifacts, instruments, and tools used throughout India's mathematical history.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p class="card-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Status:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span class="badge bg-warning text-dark"&gt;Planning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="col-md-6 mb-4"&gt;
  &lt;div class="card h-100"&gt;
    &lt;div class="card-body"&gt;
      &lt;h3 class="card-title"&gt;Translation of Key Mathematical Texts&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="card-text"&gt;We are working on translating significant mathematical texts from Sanskrit and other Indian languages into English and modern Indian languages to make them accessible to a wider audience.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p class="card-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Status:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span class="badge bg-warning text-dark"&gt;Planning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;div class="col-md-12"&gt;
    &lt;h2 class="mb-4"&gt;Upcoming Projects&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;We are in the process of developing several new research initiatives focused on the history of mathematics in India. These projects will explore various aspects of mathematical traditions, techniques, and contributions from ancient to modern times.&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;h4 class="mt-4 mb-3"&gt;Planned Focus Areas:&lt;/h4&gt;
    &lt;ul class="list-group mb-4"&gt;
      &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;i class="bi bi-book me-2"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Comparative studies of mathematical traditions across cultures&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;i class="bi bi-camera me-2"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Photographic documentation of mathematical instruments&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;i class="bi bi-people me-2"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Oral history project with contemporary Indian mathematicians&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;i class="bi bi-globe me-2"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Interactive web resources on Indian mathematical concepts&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;i class="bi bi-mortarboard me-2"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Development of curriculum materials for schools&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;

    &lt;div class="alert alert-info"&gt;
      &lt;i class="bi bi-info-circle me-2"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Interested in collaborating on any of these projects? Please &lt;a href="mailto:homi@iitgn.ac.in" class="alert-link"&gt;contact us&lt;/a&gt; to discuss potential partnerships.
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



Our Research Methodology


&lt;div class="col-md-6"&gt;
  &lt;img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x400.jpg?text=Research+Methodology" alt="Our Research Methodology" class="img-fluid rounded mb-4"&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="col-md-6"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Our research approach combines traditional historical methods with modern digital techniques:&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;ul class="list-group mb-4"&gt;
    &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Source Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt; Working directly with original manuscripts and texts&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interdisciplinary Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Bringing together historians, mathematicians, linguists, and educators&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Humanities:&lt;/strong&gt; Using computational tools to analyze and preserve historical materials&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li class="list-group-item"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Educational Outreach:&lt;/strong&gt; Translating research findings into accessible educational resources&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;This comprehensive approach ensures that our research is both academically rigorous and practically useful for education and cultural preservation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

Educational Resources



&lt;div class="col-md-8 mx-auto text-center"&gt;
  &lt;p class="lead"&gt;Access our collection of educational materials on the history of mathematics in India, including presentations, videos, and research papers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



